using Statistics
using Random
using Printf
using Logging; Logging.disable_logging(Logging.LogLevel(0))

struct configuration
    L::Int #size of box
    particles::BitArray #array indices start at 1, so particles[i+1]=1 iff (i%L,iL) contains a particle
    active::BitSet #list of active particles
end

function Base.copy(c::configuration)
    configuration(c.L,copy(c.particles),copy(c.active))
end

using Plots
rectangle(x, y) = Shape(x .+ [0.1,0.9,0.9,0.1], y .+ [0.1,0.1,0.9,0.9])

function plotconfiguration(::BitArray,L)
    plt = plot(legend=false,xticks = 0:1:L,yticks=0:1:L, xlim=(0,L), ylim=(0,L),
        yaxis=false, xaxis=false, size=(250,250), gridlinewidth=2)
    for i in findall()
        plot!(rectangle(x(i-1,L),y(i-1,L)), legend=false, color="black")
    end
    plt
end

function plotconfiguration(c::configuration)
     = c.particles
    L = c.L
    plt = plot(legend=false,xticks = 0:1:L,yticks=0:1:L, xlim=(0,L), ylim=(0,L),
        yaxis=false, xaxis=false, size=(250,250), gridlinewidth=2)
    for i in findall()
        clr = "black"
        if (i-1) in c.active
            clr = "red"
        end
        plot!(rectangle(x(i-1,L),y(i-1,L)), legend=false, color=clr)
    end
    plt
end

function x(i::Int,L::Int)
    return i % L
end
function y(i::Int,L::Int)
    return iL
end
function idx(x::Int, y::Int, L::Int)
    return x + L*y
end
function neighbors(i::Int,L::Int)
    nbrs = BitSet()
    i1=x(i,L)
    i2=y(i,L)
    if i1 > 0
        push!(nbrs,idx(i1-1,i2,L))
    end
    if i1<L-1
        push!(nbrs,idx(i1+1,i2,L))
    end
    if i2 > 0
        push!(nbrs,idx(i1,i2-1,L))
    end
    if i2<L-1
        push!(nbrs,idx(i1,i2+1,L))
    end
    return nbrs
end

In [5]:
function empty_neighbors(i::Int,c::configuration)
    nbrs = neighbors(i,c.L)
    return filter(j -> !c.particles[j+1], nbrs)
end
function occupied_neighbors(i::Int,c::configuration)
    nbrs = neighbors(i,c.L)
    return filter(j -> c.particles[j+1], nbrs)
end
function has_occupied_neighbor(i::Int,::BitArray,L::Int)
    nbrs = neighbors(i,L)
    return !isempty(filter(j -> [j+1], nbrs))
end
function has_occupied_neighbor(i::Int,c::configuration)
    return has_occupied_neighbor(i,c.particles,c.L)
end
function has_empty_neighbor(i::Int,::BitArray,L::Int)
    nbrs = neighbors(i,L)
    return !isempty(filter(j -> ![j+1], nbrs))
end
function has_empty_neighbor(i::Int,c::configuration)
    return has_empty_neighbor(i,c.particles,c.L)
end

In [6]:
function init_configuration(::BitArray)
    L = Int(sqrt(size()[1]))
    active_sites = BitSet()
    for i in 0:(L^2-1)
        if [i+1] && has_occupied_neighbor(i,,L) && has_empty_neighbor(i,,L)
            push!(active_sites,i)
        end
    end
    return configuration(L,,active_sites)
end

#move particle from i to j and update active sites
function hop(c::configuration, i::Int, j::Int)
    c.particles[i+1] = 0
    c.particles[j+1] = 1
    
    delete!(c.active,i)
    for k in occupied_neighbors(i,c)
        if !has_occupied_neighbor(k,c)
            delete!(c.active,k)
        else
            push!(c.active,k)    
        end
    end
    
    if has_occupied_neighbor(j,c)
        push!(c.active,j)
    end
    for k in occupied_neighbors(j,c)
        if has_empty_neighbor(k,c)
            push!(c.active,k)
        else
            delete!(c.active,k)
        end
    end
end

In [7]:
function single_step(c::configuration)
    if isempty(c.active) #blocked configuration
        return -1
    end
    t = 1/length(c.active) #strictly speaking this should be an exponential rv with rate length(c.active), but taking the expected value is good enough
    jump_from = rand(c.active)
    jump_to = rand(empty_neighbors(jump_from,c))
    hop(c, jump_from, jump_to)
    return t
end

function absorption_time(c::configuration, max_steps=1000000)
    t = 0
    if sum(c.particles) > c.L^2 / 2  #no absorbing state
        return -1
    end
    absorbed = false
    for i in 1:max_steps
        dt = single_step(c)
        if dt<0
            absorbed = true
            break
        end
        t += dt
    end
    if !absorbed
        t=-2 
    end
    return t
end

function random_configuration(L::Int, p::Float64)
    0 = [i < p*L^2 for i in 0:(L^2-1)]
     = BitArray(0[randperm(L^2)])
    return init_configuration()
end

function two_percolation(c::configuration)
    L2 = c.L  2
     = falses(L2^2)
    
    for i in 0:(L2^2-1)
        i1 = 2*x(i,L2)
        i2 = 2*y(i,L2)
        
        lb = idx(i1,i2,c.L)
        lt = idx(i1,i2+1,c.L)
        rb = idx(i1+1,i2,c.L)
        rt = idx(i1+1,i2+1,c.L)
        
        particles_in_square = c.particles[lb+1]+c.particles[lt+1]+c.particles[rb+1]+c.particles[rt+1]
        if particles_in_square >= 2
            [i+1] = true
        end
    end
    return 
end

#returns a configuration of the 22 squares, atcive sites are those that are connected to the bottom line
function percolation_connected_to_bottom(::BitArray,L::Int)
    active_sites = BitSet()
    for i in 0:(L-1)
        if [i+1]
            push!(active_sites,i)
        end
    end
    for t in 1:L^2
        active_sites2 = copy(active_sites)
        for i in active_sites2
            for j in neighbors(i,L)
                if [j+1]
                    push!(active_sites,j)
                end
            end
        end
    end
    return configuration(L,,active_sites)
end

function plot_percolation_process(c::configuration)
    L2 = c.L2
    perco = two_percolation(c)
    perco_bottom = percolation_connected_to_bottom(perco,L2)
    plotconfiguration(perco_bottom)
end
